{"title_page": "List of South African Airways destinations", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:South_African_Airways_Airbus_A350-941_ZS-SDF_arriving_at_JFK_Airport.jpg|thumb|South African Airways' first [[Airbus A350-900]] arriving at [[John F. Kennedy International Airport]] in [[New York City|New York]]]]\nThis is a list of '''[[South African Airways]]''' destinations, {{as of|2020|1|lc=y}}.<ref name=\"International_Timetable\" /><ref name=\"CPT-JNB_Timetable\" /><ref name=\"DUR-JNB_Timetable\" />\n\n{{as of|2016|6}}, South African Airways served eight destinations outside Africa. By that time, the top five international routes led from [[Johannesburg]] to [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York City-JFK]], [[London Heathrow]], [[Hong Kong]], [[Frankfurt]] and [[Perth]].<ref name=\"Africa Outlook: Ethiopian Airlines and Air Mauritius grow, but others face strong headwinds\" />\n\n==List==\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n!Country\n!City\n!Airport\n!Notes\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Refs\n|-\n|Angola||[[Luanda]]||[[Quatro de Fevereiro Airport]]||{{terminated}} ||align=center|<ref name=\"International_Timetable\" /><ref name=SAAreductions>[https://www.fin24.com/Companies/Industrial/saa-to-scrap-all-domestic-routes-apart-from-joburg-cape-town-20200206 SAA network reductions]</ref>\n|-\n|Argentina||[[Buenos Aires]]||[[Ministro Pistarini International Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"SAA to continue serving the Argentinean market through partnerships\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Australia||[[Melbourne]]||[[Melbourne Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=SA76/>\n|-\n|[[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]]||[[Perth Airport]]|| ||align=center|<ref name=\"International_Timetable\" />\n|-\n|[[Sydney]]||[[Sydney Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"FI1998-87\" />\n|-\n|Austria||[[Vienna]]||[[Vienna International Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"