A celebrates 50 Years of direct flights between South Africa and Mauritius; frequency increases driven by demand-side growth\" />\n|-\n|Mozambique||[[Maputo]]||[[Maputo International Airport]]|| ||align=center|<ref name=\"International_Timetable\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Namibia||[[Keetmanshoop]]||[[Keetmanshoop Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"1977/78: SAA International Network\" />\n|-\n|[[Windhoek]]||[[Hosea Kutako International Airport]]|| ||align=center|<ref name=\"International_Timetable\" />\n|-\n|Netherlands||[[Amsterdam]]||[[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"FI1998-87\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Nigeria||[[Abuja]]||[[Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/277686/south-african-airways-closes-abuja-bookings-in-ns18/|title=South African Airways closes Abuja bookings in NS18|publisher=Airlineroute.net|date=20 March 2018|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lagos]]||[[Murtala Muhammed International Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"Timetable_20161101\" />\n|-\n|Portugal||[[Lisbon]]||[[Lisbon Portela Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"FI1985-120\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Republic of the Congo||[[Brazzaville]]||[[Maya-Maya Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"Timetable_20161101\" />\n|-\n|[[Pointe-Noire]]||[[Pointe-Noire Airport]]|| ||align=center|<ref>[http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=23043&catid=74&Itemid=30 DefenceWeb.co.za - South African Airways introduces non-stop flights to Beijing; strengthens African routes]</ref>\n|-\n|Rwanda||[[Kigali]]||[[Kigali International Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"SAA to re-align its African network\"/>\n|-\n|R\u00e9union||[[Saint-Denis, R\u00e9union|Saint-Denis]]||[[Roland Garros Airport]]||{{terminated}}||align=center|<ref name=\"FI1985-120\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\