{"title_page": "WA postcode area", "text_new": "{{short description|Postcode area within the United Kingdom}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK postcode area|area_code=WA}}\nThe '''WA postcode area''', also known as the '''Warrington postcode area''',<ref>Royal Mail, ''Address Management Guide'', (2004)</ref> is a group of sixteen postcode districts in [[North West England]], within nine [[post town]]s. These cover north [[Cheshire]] (including [[Warrington]], [[Frodsham]], [[Knutsford]], [[Lymm]], [[Runcorn]] and [[Widnes]]), eastern [[Merseyside]] (including [[St Helens, Merseyside|St Helens]] and [[Newton-le-Willows]]) and small parts of [[Greater Manchester]] (including [[Altrincham]]).\n\n__TOC__\n{{clear}}\n\n==Coverage==\nThe approximate coverage of the postcode districts:\n\n{{postcode area table start}}\n|-\n! WA1\n| WARRINGTON\n| [[Warrington]], Town Centre, [[Woolston, Warrington|Woolston]], Paddington, Orford\n| [[Warrington Borough Council|Warrington]]\n|-\n! WA2\n| WARRINGTON\n| [[Warrington]], , [[Dallam, Warrington|Dallam]], [[Longford, Warrington|Longford]], [[Orford, Cheshire|Orford]], [[Padgate]], [[Winwick, Cheshire|Winwick]]\n| Warrington\n|-\n! WA3\n| WARRINGTON\n| <!-- sector details too confusing to list here: WA3(1,2) -->[[Lowton]], <!-- sector details too confusing to list here: WA3(3) -->[[Golborne]], <!-- sector details too confusing to list here: WA3(4,5,6,7) -->[[Birchwood]], [[Rixton with Glazebrook]], [[Culcheth]]\n| [[Metropolitan Borough of Wigan|Wigan]], Warrington\n|-\n! WA4\n| WARRINGTON\n| [[Warrington]], [[Latchford]], [[Stockton Heath]], [[Appleton, Warrington|Appleton]], [[Grappenhall]], [[Daresbury]], [[Antrobus, Cheshire|Antrobus]] (part), [[Moore, Cheshire|Moore]], [[Walton, Cheshire|Walton]], [[Preston on the Hill]]\n| Warrington, [[Borough of Halton|Halton]], [[Cheshire West and Chester]]\n\n|-\n! WA5\n| WARRINGTON\n| [[Warrington]], <!-- sector details too confusing to list here: WA5(4) -->[[Burtonwood]], [[Westbrook, Warrington|Westbrook]], [[Penketh]], [[Great Sankey]], White Cross\n| Warrington\n|-\n! WA6\n| FRODSHAM\n| [[Frodsham]], [[Helsby]]\n| Cheshire West and Chester\n|-\n! WA7\n| RUNCORN\n| [[Runcorn]]\n| Halton\n|-\n! WA8\n| WIDNES\n| [[Widnes]], [[Cronton]]\n| Halton, [[Metropolitan Borough of Knowsley|Knowsley]]\n|-\n! WA9\n| ST. HELENS\n| [[Clock Face, Merseyside|Clock Face]], [[Sutton, Merseyside|Sutton]], [[Thatto Heath]]\n| [[Metropolitan Borough of St Helens|St Helens]]\n|-\n! WA10\n| ST. HELENS\n| [[Eccleston, St Helens|Eccleston]], [[St Helens, Merseyside|St. Helens]], West Park\n| St Helens\n|-\n! WA11\n| ST. HELENS\n| [[Crank, Merseyside|Crank]], [[Haydock]], [[Moss Bank]], [[Rainford]]\n| St Helens\n|-\n! WA12\n| NEWTON-LE-WILLOWS\n| [[Newton-le-Willows]], [[Earlestown]]\n| St Helens\n|-\n! WA13\n| LYMM\n| [[Lymm]], [[Lymm|Statham]], [[Warburton, Greater Manchester|Warburton]]\n| Warrington, [[Trafford]]\n|-\n! WA14\n| ALTRINCHAM\n| [[Altrincham]], [[Bowdon, Greater Manchester|Bowdon]], [[Broadheath, Greater Manchester|Broadheath]], [[Dunham Town]], [[Timperley]], [[Dunham Massey]], [[Little Bollington]]\n| Trafford, [[Cheshire East]]\n|-\n! WA15\n| ALTRINCHAM\n| [[Altrincham]], [[Ashley, Cheshire|Ashley]], [[Hale, Greater Manchester|Hale]], [[Hale Barns]], [[Timperley]], [[Ringway, Greater Manchester|Ringway]]\n| Trafford, [[Manchester City Council|Manchester]], Cheshire East\n|-\n! WA16\n| KNUTSFORD\n| [[High Legh]], [[Knutsford]], [[Mobberley]], [[Ollerton, Cheshire|Ollerton]], [[Antrobus, Cheshire|Antrobus]] (part)\n| Cheshire East, Cheshire West and Chester\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|WA55\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|WARRINGTON\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|''non-geographic''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|WA88\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|WIDNES\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|\n| style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"|''non-geographic''\n|}\n\nThe Frodsham post town was introduced in June 1999; the post town for WA6 had previously been Warrington.<ref>[ftp://ftp.royalmail.com/Downloads/public/ctf/rm/21sep06_MajorRecodes_to_1999.doc Royal Mail (ftp site)]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} - Royal Mail major recode historical information - 1990 to 1999</ref>\n\n==Map==\n{{Attached KML|display=inline}}\n{{Postcode area imagemap|map=WA postcode area}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Postcode Address File]]\n*[[List of postcode areas in the United Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.poweredbypaf.com/  Royal Mail's Postcode Address File]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20180926234202/https://www.poweredbypaf.com/how-the-royal-mail-postcode-address-file-paf-helps-organisations-verify-their-customers-identities/ A quick introduction to Royal Mail's Postcode Address File (PAF)]\n*[http://www.manchester2002-uk.com/towns/postcodes.html Postcodes of Greater Manchester]\n\n{{Postcode areas in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:Warrington]]\n[[Category:Postcode areas covering North West England]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Postcode area within the United Kingdom}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK postcode area|area_code=WA}}\nThe '''WA postcode area''', also known as the '''Warrington postcode area''',<ref>Royal Mail, ''Address Management Guide'', (2004)</ref> is a group of sixteen postcode districts in [[North West England]], within nine [[post town]]s. These cover north [[Cheshire]] (including [[Warrington]], [[Frodsham]], [[Knutsford]], [[Lymm]], [[Runcorn]] and [[Widnes]]), eastern [[Merseyside]] (including [[St Helens, Merseyside|St Helens]] and [[Newton-le-Willows]]) and small parts of [[Greater Manchester]] (including [[Altrincham]]).\n\n__TOC__\n{{clear}}\n\n==Coverage==\nThe approximate coverage of the postcode districts:\n\n{{postcode area table start}}\n|-\n! WA1\n| WARRINGTON\n| [[Warrington]], Town Centre, [[Woolston, Warrington|Woolston]], Paddingto